{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":280,"text":"Well, as many of you know,"},{"time":1839,"text":"the results of the recent\nelection were as follows:"},{"time":5160,"text":"Hillary Clinton, the Democratic candidate"},{"time":7800,"text":"won a landslide victory"},{"time":9720,"text":"with 52 percent of the overall vote."},{"time":12520,"text":"Jill Stein, the Green candidate,"},{"time":14800,"text":"came a distant second, with 19 percent."},{"time":18080,"text":"Donald J. Trump, the Republic candidate,"},{"time":20560,"text":"was hot on her heels with 14 percent,"},{"time":23680,"text":"and the remainder of the vote\nwere shared between abstainers"},{"time":27120,"text":"and Gary Johnson,\nthe Libertarian candidate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33260,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35360,"text":"Now, what parallel universe\ndo you suppose I live in?"},{"time":40760,"text":"Well, I don't live in a parallel universe."},{"time":42800,"text":"I live in the world,\nand that is how the world voted."},{"time":47160,"text":"So let me take you back\nand explain what I mean by that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50800,"text":"In June this year,"},{"time":52040,"text":"I launched something\ncalled the Global Vote."},{"time":54800,"text":"And the Global Vote\ndoes exactly what it says on the tin."},{"time":58640,"text":"For the first time in history,"},{"time":60320,"text":"it lets anybody, anywhere in the world,"},{"time":63080,"text":"vote in the elections\nof other people's countries."},{"time":67040,"text":"Now, why would you do that?"},{"time":69120,"text":"What's the point?"},{"time":70760,"text":"Well, let me show you what it looks like."},{"time":73120,"text":"You go to a website,"},{"time":75800,"text":"rather a beautiful website,"},{"time":77840,"text":"and then you select an election."},{"time":80680,"text":"Here's a bunch that we've already covered."},{"time":83960,"text":"We do about one a month, or thereabouts."},{"time":87120,"text":"So you can see Bulgaria,\nthe United States of America,"},{"time":89960,"text":"Secretary-General of the United Nations,"},{"time":92480,"text":"the Brexit referendum at the end there."},{"time":95440,"text":"You select the election\nthat you're interested in,"},{"time":98240,"text":"and you pick the candidates."},{"time":101520,"text":"These are the candidates\nfrom the recent presidential election"},{"time":104480,"text":"in the tiny island nation\nof São Tomé and Príncipe,"},{"time":107600,"text":"199,000 inhabitants,"},{"time":110000,"text":"off the coast of West Africa."},{"time":112520,"text":"And then you can look at the brief summary\nof each of those candidates"},{"time":117040,"text":"which I dearly hope is very neutral,"},{"time":119560,"text":"very informative and very succinct."},{"time":122400,"text":"And when you've found\nthe one you like, you vote."},{"time":125640,"text":"These were the candidates"},{"time":127200,"text":"in the recent Icelandic\npresidential election,"},{"time":130080,"text":"and that's the way it goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132920,"text":"So why on earth would you want to vote\nin another country's election?"},{"time":138720,"text":"Well, the reason\nthat you wouldn't want to do it,"},{"time":141840,"text":"let me reassure you,"},{"time":143080,"text":"is in order to interfere in the democratic\nprocesses of another country."},{"time":147000,"text":"That's not the purpose at all."},{"time":148680,"text":"In fact, you can't,"},{"time":150120,"text":"because usually what I do\nis I release the results"},{"time":152600,"text":"after the electorate in each\nindividual country has already voted,"},{"time":156160,"text":"so there's no way that we could\ninterfere in that process."},{"time":159000,"text":"But more importantly,"},{"time":160400,"text":"I'm not particularly interested"},{"time":162000,"text":"in the domestic issues\nof individual countries."},{"time":164280,"text":"That's not what we're voting on."},{"time":166680,"text":"So what Donald J. Trump or Hillary Clinton\nproposed to do for the Americans"},{"time":170640,"text":"is frankly none of our business."},{"time":172680,"text":"That's something that only\nthe Americans can vote on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175720,"text":"No, in the global vote,\nyou're only considering one aspect of it,"},{"time":179280,"text":"which is what are those leaders\ngoing to do for the rest of us?"},{"time":183480,"text":"And that's so very important\nbecause we live,"},{"time":186160,"text":"as no doubt you're sick\nof hearing people tell you,"},{"time":188600,"text":"in a globalized, hyperconnected,\nmassively interdependent world"},{"time":193880,"text":"where the political decisions\nof people in other countries"},{"time":196640,"text":"can and will have an impact on our lives"},{"time":198880,"text":"no matter who we are,\nno matter where we live."},{"time":202440,"text":"Like the wings of the butterfly"},{"time":204320,"text":"beating on one side of the Pacific"},{"time":206640,"text":"that can apparently create\na hurricane on the other side,"},{"time":210200,"text":"so it is with the world\nthat we live in today"},{"time":212880,"text":"and the world of politics."},{"time":214600,"text":"There is no longer a dividing line between\ndomestic and international affairs."},{"time":219920,"text":"Any country, no matter how small,"},{"time":222360,"text":"even if it's São Tomé and Príncipe,"},{"time":224440,"text":"could produce the next Nelson Mandela"},{"time":227000,"text":"or the next Stalin."},{"time":229640,"text":"They could pollute the atmosphere\nand the oceans, which belong to all of us,"},{"time":233640,"text":"or they could be responsible\nand they could help all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237600,"text":"And yet, the system is so strange"},{"time":240720,"text":"because the system hasn't caught up\nwith this globalized reality."},{"time":244440,"text":"Only a small number of people\nare allowed to vote for those leaders,"},{"time":247680,"text":"even though their impact is gigantic"},{"time":249760,"text":"and almost universal."},{"time":252040,"text":"What number was it?"},{"time":253480,"text":"140 million Americans voted"},{"time":256040,"text":"for the next president\nof the United States,"},{"time":258320,"text":"and yet, as all of us knows,\nin a few weeks time,"},{"time":261279,"text":"somebody is going to hand over\nthe nuclear launch codes"},{"time":263920,"text":"to Donald J. Trump."},{"time":265720,"text":"Now, if that isn't having\na potential impact on all of us,"},{"time":268560,"text":"I don't know what is."},{"time":270520,"text":"Similarly, the election\nfor the referendum on the Brexit vote,"},{"time":277200,"text":"a small number of millions\nof British people voted on that,"},{"time":280640,"text":"but the outcome of the vote,\nwhichever way it went,"},{"time":283360,"text":"would have had a significant impact"},{"time":285080,"text":"on the lives of tens, hundreds of millions\nof people around the world."},{"time":289520,"text":"And yet, only a tiny number could vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291960,"text":"What kind of democracy is that?"},{"time":294600,"text":"Huge decisions that affect all of us"},{"time":296360,"text":"being decided by relatively\nvery small numbers of people."},{"time":300240,"text":"And I don't know about you,"},{"time":301600,"text":"but I don't think\nthat sounds very democratic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304360,"text":"So I'm trying to clear it up."},{"time":306160,"text":"But as I say,"},{"time":307640,"text":"we don't ask about domestic questions."},{"time":309520,"text":"In fact, I only ever ask two questions\nof all of the candidates."},{"time":312600,"text":"I send them the same\ntwo questions every single time."},{"time":315120,"text":"I say, one,"},{"time":316560,"text":"if you get elected, what are you\ngoing to do for the rest of us,"},{"time":319720,"text":"for the remainder of the seven billion\nwho live on this planet?"},{"time":323160,"text":"Second question:"},{"time":325120,"text":"What is your vision\nfor your country's future in the world?"},{"time":328360,"text":"What role do you see it playing?"},{"time":330560,"text":"Every candidate,\nI send them those questions."},{"time":333360,"text":"They don't all answer. Don't get me wrong."},{"time":335480,"text":"I reckon if you're standing"},{"time":337280,"text":"to become the next president\nof the United States,"},{"time":339680,"text":"you're probably pretty tied up\nmost of the time,"},{"time":342080,"text":"so I'm not altogether surprised\nthat they don't all answer, but many do."},{"time":346160,"text":"More every time."},{"time":347680,"text":"And some of them do much more than answer."},{"time":349760,"text":"Some of them answer in the most\nenthusiastic and most exciting way"},{"time":352920,"text":"you could imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354160,"text":"I just want to say a word here\nfor Saviour Chishimba,"},{"time":356680,"text":"who was one of the candidates"},{"time":358120,"text":"in the recent Zambian\npresidential election."},{"time":360400,"text":"His answers to those two questions\nwere basically an 18-page dissertation"},{"time":364960,"text":"on his view of Zambia's\npotential role in the world"},{"time":368640,"text":"and in the international community."},{"time":370680,"text":"I posted it on the website\nso anybody could read it."},{"time":373920,"text":"Now, Saviour won the global vote,"},{"time":376960,"text":"but he didn't win the Zambian election."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379320,"text":"So I found myself wondering,"},{"time":380720,"text":"what am I going to do\nwith this extraordinary group of people?"},{"time":383680,"text":"I've got some wonderful people here\nwho won the global vote."},{"time":386560,"text":"We always get it wrong, by the way."},{"time":388280,"text":"The one that we elect"},{"time":389520,"text":"is never the person who's elected\nby the domestic electorate."},{"time":393640,"text":"That may be partly because\nwe always seem to go for the woman."},{"time":397400,"text":"But I think it may also be a sign"},{"time":399560,"text":"that the domestic electorate\nis still thinking very nationally."},{"time":403160,"text":"They're still thinking very inwardly."},{"time":405320,"text":"They're still asking themselves:\nWhat's in it for me? ..."},{"time":408840,"text":"instead of what\nthey should be asking today,"},{"time":410960,"text":"which is, what's in it for we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"But there you go."},{"time":415240,"text":"So suggestions, please, not right now,"},{"time":417400,"text":"but send me an email if you've got an idea"},{"time":419424,"text":"about what we can do\nwith this amazing team of glorious losers."},{"time":422700,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":423800,"text":"We've got Saviour Chishimba,\nwho I mentioned before."},{"time":426280,"text":"We've got Halla Tómasdóttir,"},{"time":427680,"text":"who was the runner up\nin the Icelandic presidential election."},{"time":430600,"text":"Many of you may have seen\nher amazing talk at TEDWomen"},{"time":433320,"text":"just a few weeks ago"},{"time":434560,"text":"where she spoke about the need\nfor more women to get into politics."},{"time":438160,"text":"We've got Maria das Neves\nfrom São Tomé and Príncipe."},{"time":441520,"text":"We've got Hillary Clinton."},{"time":443160,"text":"I don't know if she's available."},{"time":445240,"text":"We've got Jill Stein."},{"time":447480,"text":"And we covered also the election"},{"time":450360,"text":"for the next Secretary-General\nof the United Nations."},{"time":453465,"text":"We've got the ex-prime minister\nof New Zealand,"},{"time":455680,"text":"who would be a wonderful\nmember of the team."},{"time":457800,"text":"So I think maybe those people,"},{"time":459320,"text":"the glorious loser's club,\ncould travel around the world"},{"time":462000,"text":"wherever there's an election"},{"time":463400,"text":"and remind people\nof the necessity in our modern age"},{"time":466800,"text":"of thinking a little bit outwards"},{"time":468440,"text":"and thinking of\nthe international consequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472440,"text":"So what comes next for the global vote?"},{"time":474360,"text":"Well, obviously,"},{"time":476160,"text":"the Donald and Hillary show\nis a bit of a difficult one to follow,"},{"time":480640,"text":"but there are some other\nreally important elections coming up."},{"time":483600,"text":"In fact, they seem to be multiplying."},{"time":485440,"text":"There's something going on,\nI'm sure you've noticed, in the world."},{"time":488600,"text":"And the next row of elections\nare all critically important."},{"time":493280,"text":"In just a few day's time"},{"time":494800,"text":"we've got the rerun\nof the Austrian presidential election,"},{"time":497880,"text":"with the prospect of Norbert Hofer"},{"time":499680,"text":"becoming what is commonly described"},{"time":501680,"text":"as the first far-right head of state\nin Europe since the Second World War."},{"time":506280,"text":"Next year we've got Germany,"},{"time":507720,"text":"we've got France,"},{"time":508960,"text":"we've got presidential elections in Iran"},{"time":511120,"text":"and a dozen others."},{"time":512919,"text":"It doesn't get less important."},{"time":515080,"text":"It gets more and more important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518400,"text":"Clearly, the global vote\nis not a stand-alone project."},{"time":522200,"text":"It's not just there on its own."},{"time":524760,"text":"It has some background."},{"time":526040,"text":"It's part of a project\nwhich I launched back in 2014,"},{"time":530080,"text":"which I call the Good Country."},{"time":532440,"text":"The idea of the Good Country\nis basically very simple."},{"time":535840,"text":"It's my simple diagnosis\nof what's wrong with the world"},{"time":539320,"text":"and how we can fix it."},{"time":541800,"text":"What's wrong with the world\nI've already hinted at."},{"time":544240,"text":"Basically, we face\nan enormous and growing number"},{"time":547000,"text":"of gigantic, existential\nglobal challenges:"},{"time":550200,"text":"climate change, human rights abuses,"},{"time":552880,"text":"mass migration, terrorism,\neconomic chaos, weapons proliferation."},{"time":558080,"text":"All of these problems\nwhich threaten to wipe us out"},{"time":561280,"text":"are by their very nature\nglobalized problems."},{"time":563440,"text":"No individual country has the capability\nof tackling them on its own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568760,"text":"And so very obviously"},{"time":570520,"text":"we have to cooperate\nand we have to collaborate as nations"},{"time":574160,"text":"if we're going to solve these problems."},{"time":576560,"text":"It's so obvious, and yet we don't."},{"time":579880,"text":"We don't do it nearly often enough."},{"time":582640,"text":"Most of the time,\ncountries still persist in behaving"},{"time":586240,"text":"as if they were warring, selfish tribes\nbattling against each other,"},{"time":590920,"text":"much as they have done\nsince the nation-state was invented"},{"time":593680,"text":"hundreds of years ago."},{"time":595280,"text":"And this has got to change."},{"time":597440,"text":"This is not a change in political systems\nor a change in ideology."},{"time":600800,"text":"This is a change in culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602760,"text":"We, all of us, have to understand"},{"time":605640,"text":"that thinking inwards is not the solution\nto the world's problems."},{"time":609680,"text":"We have to learn how to cooperate\nand collaborate a great deal more"},{"time":613680,"text":"and compete just a tiny bit less."},{"time":617200,"text":"Otherwise things\nare going to carry on getting bad"},{"time":619600,"text":"and they're going to get much worse,\nmuch sooner than we anticipate."},{"time":623760,"text":"This change will only happen"},{"time":625680,"text":"if we ordinary people"},{"time":627440,"text":"tell our politicians\nthat things have changed."},{"time":630280,"text":"We have to tell them\nthat the culture has changed."},{"time":632840,"text":"We have to tell them\nthat they've got a new mandate."},{"time":635440,"text":"The old mandate\nwas very simple and very single:"},{"time":638360,"text":"if you're in a position\nof power or authority,"},{"time":640560,"text":"you're responsible for your own people\nand your own tiny slice of territory,"},{"time":644200,"text":"and that's it."},{"time":645440,"text":"And if in order to do\nthe best thing for your own people,"},{"time":648160,"text":"you screw over everybody else\non the planet, that's even better."},{"time":651240,"text":"That's considered to be a bit macho."},{"time":653000,"text":"Today, I think everybody\nin a position of power and responsibility"},{"time":656400,"text":"has got a dual mandate,"},{"time":658040,"text":"which says if you're in a position\nof power and responsibility,"},{"time":661040,"text":"you're responsible for your own people"},{"time":662920,"text":"and for every single man, woman,\nchild and animal on the planet."},{"time":667280,"text":"You're responsible\nfor your own slice of territory"},{"time":669680,"text":"and for every single square mile\nof the earth's surface"},{"time":673400,"text":"and the atmosphere above it."},{"time":674800,"text":"And if you don't like that responsibility,\nyou should not be in power."},{"time":678160,"text":"That for me is the rule of the modern age,"},{"time":680240,"text":"and that's the message that we've got\nto get across to our politicians,"},{"time":683640,"text":"and show them that that's the way\nthings are done these days."},{"time":686960,"text":"Otherwise, we're all screwed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690040,"text":"I don't have a problem, actually,"},{"time":691680,"text":"with Donald Trump's credo\nof \"America first.\""},{"time":694640,"text":"It seems to me that that's\na pretty banal statement"},{"time":697080,"text":"of what politicians have always done\nand probably should always do."},{"time":700280,"text":"Of course they're elected to represent\nthe interests of their own people."},{"time":704480,"text":"But what I find so boring\nand so old-fashioned"},{"time":707480,"text":"and so unimaginative\nabout his take on that"},{"time":710240,"text":"is that America first\nmeans everyone else last,"},{"time":714280,"text":"that making America great again\nmeans making everybody else small again,"},{"time":718480,"text":"and it's just not true."},{"time":720640,"text":"In my job as a policy advisor\nover the last 20 years or so,"},{"time":723560,"text":"I've seen so many hundreds\nof examples of policies"},{"time":727200,"text":"that harmonize the international\nand the domestic needs,"},{"time":730760,"text":"and they make better policy."},{"time":732760,"text":"I'm not asking nations\nto be altruistic or self-sacrificing."},{"time":736360,"text":"That would be ridiculous."},{"time":737720,"text":"No nation would ever do that."},{"time":739840,"text":"I'm asking them to wake up and understand\nthat we need a new form of governance,"},{"time":743680,"text":"which is possible"},{"time":745640,"text":"and which harmonizes those two needs,"},{"time":747480,"text":"those good for our own people\nand those good for everybody else."},{"time":751520,"text":"Since the US election and since Brexit"},{"time":753760,"text":"it's become more and more obvious to me"},{"time":756160,"text":"that those old distinctions\nof left wing and right wing"},{"time":758800,"text":"no longer make sense."},{"time":760120,"text":"They really don't fit the pattern."},{"time":762760,"text":"What does seem to matter today"},{"time":765080,"text":"is very simple,"},{"time":766720,"text":"whether your view of the world is"},{"time":768920,"text":"that you take comfort\nfrom looking inwards and backwards,"},{"time":772640,"text":"or whether, like me, you find hope\nin looking forwards and outwards."},{"time":778240,"text":"That's the new politics."},{"time":779760,"text":"That's the new division that is\nsplitting the world right down the middle."},{"time":784800,"text":"Now, that may sound judgmental,\nbut it's not meant to be."},{"time":787720,"text":"I don't at all misunderstand"},{"time":789680,"text":"why so many people find their comfort\nin looking inwards and backwards."},{"time":794560,"text":"When times are difficult,\nwhen you're short of money,"},{"time":797080,"text":"when you're feeling\ninsecure and vulnerable,"},{"time":799200,"text":"it's almost a natural\nhuman tendency to turn inwards,"},{"time":801720,"text":"to think of your own needs"},{"time":803760,"text":"and to discard everybody else's,"},{"time":805880,"text":"and perhaps to start to imagine\nthat the past was somehow better"},{"time":809640,"text":"than the present or the future\ncould ever be."},{"time":812720,"text":"But I happen to believe\nthat that's a dead end."},{"time":815200,"text":"History shows us that it's a dead end."},{"time":817480,"text":"When people turn inwards\nand turn backwards,"},{"time":819640,"text":"human progress becomes reversed"},{"time":821440,"text":"and things get worse for everybody\nvery quickly indeed."},{"time":826720,"text":"If you're like me"},{"time":828160,"text":"and you believe in forwards and outwards,"},{"time":830880,"text":"and you believe that the best thing\nabout humanity is its diversity,"},{"time":835600,"text":"and the best thing about globalization"},{"time":838400,"text":"is the way that it stirs up\nthat diversity, that cultural mixture"},{"time":842720,"text":"to make something more creative,\nmore exciting, more productive"},{"time":845760,"text":"than there's ever been before\nin human history,"},{"time":848720,"text":"then, my friends,\nwe've got a job on our hands,"},{"time":852160,"text":"because the inwards and backwards brigade"},{"time":855080,"text":"are uniting as never before,"},{"time":857640,"text":"and that creed of inwards and backwards,"},{"time":859600,"text":"that fear, that anxiety,"},{"time":863040,"text":"playing on the simplest instincts,"},{"time":864880,"text":"is sweeping across the world."},{"time":867440,"text":"Those of us who believe,"},{"time":869400,"text":"as I believe, in forwards and outwards,"},{"time":872160,"text":"we have to get ourselves organized,"},{"time":875080,"text":"because time is running out\nvery, very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880240,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}